rComments: I have taken classes with him every year. He is extremely helpful and approachable. He explains concepts clearly and if you don't get it, he will spend the time with you until you do. His assignments and midterms are fair, while the final is brutal, but he gives fair warning and provides help before the exam.
best professor you will ever meet. He always willing to help no matter what. Hes will always help you till you get it

I found that he was really helpful when I asked him to explain concepts I didn't understand during class. He was patient and never made me feel stupid for asking some of what I later thought to be very stupid. His general approach in this course is to make the midterm very easy and the final, a killer. Still, very easy to do well here. Dedication.

one of the best professor in u of t, very patient, helpful,and nice. I like his way of explaining ideas, very clear and conprehensive!
